{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"e958e63e-f668-4e6c-8563-4b198ece5eeb","content":"Here's the analysis of this project's evaluation performance issues:\n\n### 1. **File I/O Property Function** (most impactful)\n**Line 13 of `EvalHeavy.csproj`:**\n```xml\n<BuildNotes>$([System.IO.File]::ReadAllText('build-notes.txt'))</BuildNotes>\n```\nUsing `System.IO.File::ReadAllText()` during evaluation forces synchronous disk I/O on every single evaluation pass. This blocks the MSBuild evaluation thread. If you need file content, read it in a target at execution time instead.\n\n### 2. **Overly Broad Glob Pattern**\n**Line 9:**\n```xml\n<AdditionalFiles Include=\"**\\*.*\" Exclude=\"**\\bin\\**;**\\obj\\**\" />\n```\n`**\\*.*` walks the entire directory tree. As the project grows (or if `node_modules`, `.git`, or other large directories exist), this becomes increasingly expensive. Use `DefaultItemExcludes` to prune large directories, or narrow the glob to specific extensions/subdirectories.\n\n### 3. **Chained Import Depth**\n`EvalHeavy.csproj → level1.props → level2.props → level3.props` creates a 3-deep import chain. This is minor at 3 levels, but the pattern scales poorly — deep chains increase evaluation time and make preprocessing (`/pp`) output harder to reason about.\n\n### Recommended Fixes\n| Issue | Fix |\n|---|---|\n| `File::ReadAllText` | Move to a target with `Inputs/Outputs` so it only runs at build time |\n| `**\\*.*` glob | Restrict to specific extensions (e.g., `**\\*.txt`) or add large dirs to `DefaultItemExcludes` |\n| Import chain | Flatten into a single `.props` if settings are simple |\n\nThe file-read property function is the most critical issue — it adds I/O cost to every evaluation, including IDE background evaluations in Visual Studio.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"f8ddf03b-760d-483a-b775-ad8460e8cddb","outputTokens":479,"requestId":"2806:23D333:32AA731:37782E9:69FBE999"},"id":"3105ce7c-e164-4761-bf4e-2a98f0d07485","timestamp":"2026-05-07T01:23:51.498Z","parentId":"21363723-b414-4a47-a7d9-6941bf4ebc67"}
